SIMPLE: mightiness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mightiness
<hw>Might"i*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of
being mighty; possession of might; power; greatness; high
dignity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How soon this <qex>mightiness</qex> meets misery.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Highness; excellency; -- with a possessive pronoun,
a title of dignity; <as>as, their high
<ex>mightinesses</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mightless</ent>⟦br⟧
